<body>
    <h1>Oracle Smart View Installation Guide</h1>

    <div class="step step1">
        <h2>Step 1: Download & Install Oracle Smart View</h2>

        <div class="step step1-1">
            <h3>Step 1.1: Download Oracle Smart View</h3>

            <div class="option">
                <h4>Option 1: Use Oracle Link</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to the Financial Reporting Center and select the <strong>Open Workspace for Financial Reports</strong> task.</li>
                    <li>In the Enterprise Performance Management System Workspace, select <strong>Tools > Install > Smart View</strong>.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="option">
                <h4>Option 2: Use Search Engine</h4>
                <p>In your favourite search engine, type <em>"Oracle Smart View for Office Downloads"</em> and click on the Oracle Smart View for Office Downloads link. Follow the instructions.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step step1-2">
            <h3>Step 1.2: Install Oracle Smart View</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Oracle Download manager tool will be downloaded initially. Using the tool, download the Smart View Installation executable.</li>
                <li>Double click on Smart View Executable to install the Plugin Software.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step step2">
        <h2>Step 2: Enable Oracle Smart View Plugin</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Once the software is successfully installed, open Microsoft Excel Application and navigate to <strong>File > Options > Add-ins</strong>.</li>
            <li>Under the Manage section, select <strong>COM Add-ins</strong> and click on the Go button.</li>
            <li>Select <strong>Oracle Smart View For Office</strong> and click OK.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>This step will enable Smart View Plugin for Excel.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step step3">
        <h2>Step 3: Connect to Fusion Applications</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Open Excel. Navigate to the <strong>Smart View menu > Options</strong>.</li>
            <li>Click the Options button and select the Advanced option.</li>
            <li>Paste the URL in the Shared Connections URL field. Click OK.</li>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Panel > Shared Connections</strong> and the Oracle Applications Window will open. Sign in to Fusion Applications.</li>
            <li>After successful login, navigate to <strong>Shared Connections > Select > Oracle Essbase</strong> > Under Essbase Cluster > Select <strong>Chart of Accounts Name</strong> specific to your organisation.</li>
            <li>Click On Connect.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</body>
